            <title>[JCR-2052] XPath QueryFormat may produce malformed XPath statement</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2052</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>When the query tree contains select properties *and* an order by clause, then the XPath QueryFormat will produce a malformed XPath statement.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
E.g.:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
//element(*, foo)/(@a|@b) order by @bar&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
round trips to:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
//element(*, foo) order by @bar/(@a|@b)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
